Any vulnerabilities affecting the main Confluence website content will also affect the administration section of Confluence.

h3. Recommendation
Consider separating the website administration from the website presentation, ideally through the use of separate domains. Also consider restricting access to this functionality, so that only internal or trusted IP addresses are permitted to access the administrative access.

h3. *Steps to replicate*
# Create a page and insert the following log extract
{code}
2016-02-16 23:37:05,328 WARN [http-nio-8090-exec-7] [atlassian.config.xml.AbstractDom4jXmlConfigurationPersister]
{code}
# Search for the string "AbstractDom" and notice that it cannot be found.
# Search for the page title or the entire string "atlassian.config.xml.AbstractDom4jXmlConfigurationPersister" and it's searchable.

h3. *Thing(s) to note*
- Reindex doesn't help.
- Inserting wild cards also doesn't help. Example 
{code:java}
*AbstractDom*
{code}

