In Outlook 2013 or higher , Confluence email notification shows "lanage notifications" instead of "Manage notifications"

h3. Symptom

The API is documented on [Confdev|https://developer.atlassian.com/confdev/plugin-cookbook/adding-feature-discovery-to-your-plugin] but it is not usable:
{code}
    void register(FeatureCompleteKey featureCompleteKey);
{code}

It triggers:
{code}
java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.featurediscovery.FeatureCompleteKey not found
{code}

h3. Cause

{{confluence-feature-discovery-plugin}} exports {{com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.featurediscovery.service}}, but it doesn't export {{com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.featurediscovery}}. So the class {{FeatureDiscoveryService}} is visible to other plugins, but not {{FeatureCompleteKey}}.

h3. How to fix

Someone will have to change the {{pom.xml}} of {{confluence-feature-discovery-plugin}} and add the package in the {{<ExportPackage>}} section.

